# 3. Service & Version Detection

## Objective

Identify services and software versions running on open ports.

## Command

```bash
nmap -sV <TARGET-IP>
```

## Output File

```bash
nmap -sV <TARGET-IP> -oN raw-output/service-version.txt
```

## Explanation

- `-sV` probes each open port.
- Detects service name.
- Detects software version.
- Helps identify outdated or vulnerable software.

